To set a custom action view for a MenuItem (which replaces the default item appearance when shown as an action), use one of these approaches:

- Set the action view using a layout resource
MenuItem item = menu.findItem(R.id.action_item);
item.setActionView(R.layout.action_view_layout);

- Set the action view using an existing View
View customView = LayoutInflater.from(context).inflate(R.layout.action_view_layout, null);
item.setActionView(customView);

To access and interact with the action view later:
View actionView = item.getActionView();
// Example: find and configure widgets inside the action view
ImageButton button = actionView.findViewById(R.id.btn_action);
button.setOnClickListener(v -> {
    // handle action
});

Notes:
- After setting an action view, the default item presentation is replaced when displayed as an action in a parent toolbar/menu.
- You can still call getActionView() to update or reset its state, or call collapseActionView()/expandActionView() if needed. 
- If you need to revert to the default item view, call item.setActionView(null).
